  "mixStrategy": "This ambient sleep score is built around the progression Fsus2 \u2192 Bbmaj7 \u2192 Fmaj7 \u2192 Dm, moving in slow modal shifts across 45 seconds (~6 segments of ~7.5s each). FREQUENCY SEPARATION: The Warm Pad bass (GM 89) anchors the sub-bass/bass range (MIDI 29-43, ~50-200Hz) with long 8-16s drone roots, providing a dark, warm foundation. The Choir Pad chords (GM 91) fill the low-mid to mid range (MIDI 48-67, ~300Hz-1.5kHz) with open sus2/maj7 voicings (root-5th-9th spacing), creating harmonic body without clutter. The New Age Pad melody (GM 88) floats in the high-mid/presence range (MIDI 65-79, ~1-4kHz) with sparse, singing phrases of 4-8s sustains that trace chord tones on strong beats and Lydian scale passing tones between. The Sweep Pad texture (GM 95) shimmers in the upper presence range (MIDI 72-84, ~3-8kHz) with ultra-sparse, ghostly long tones adding air and dimension. ENERGY ARC: All tracks breathe together \u2014 starting very sparse and quiet (vel 25-35), gently swelling to modest warmth mid-piece (vel 35-50), then fading back to near-silence. Bass and chords change on the same beats; melody anticipates or echoes chord changes with approach tones. No rhythmic pulse exists \u2014 notes drift in with staggered entries creating gentle overlaps. The overall effect is a dark, enveloping cloud of sound where each layer occupies its own sonic space: bass = earth, chords = body, melody = breath, texture = sky.",
